    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-12T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-12T08:00:00-05:00" n="391"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d391">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/1530: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-12T22:00:00+09:00"
                            >June 12, 1940—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 12—10:18 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>447. My 429, June 10, 6 p.m.<note n="65" xml:id="d391fn65">Not printed, but see
                        memoranda from the Ambassador in Japan, June 10, <ref
                            target="frus1931-41v02#pg_67">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, pp. 67</ref>, <ref
                            target="frus1931-41v02#pg_71">71</ref>, <ref
                            target="frus1931-41v02#pg_73">73</ref>, and <ref
                            target="frus1931-41v02#pg_75">75</ref>.</note> The Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs has sent me as an “informal, oral and unofficial statement” a document
                    marked strictly confidential, the text of which in translation is contained in
                    our immediately following telegram 4[<hi rend="italic">48</hi>], June 12, 11
                        p.m.<note n="66" xml:id="d391fn66">
                        <ref target="frus1931-41v02#pg_79">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 79</ref>.</note> He wishes me to
                    understand that it does not commit his Government in any way but that it will
                    serve to indicate certain thoughts which have occurred to him following our
                    conversation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
